{
  "domain": "nycgovparks.org",
  "agency": "New York City Department of Parks & Recreation (NYC Parks)",
  "assessment_date": "2026-07-13",
  "method": "Bounded outside-in crawl (browser UA, robots-respecting). Landing pages and a representative sample of listing/form/database pages fetched and analyzed for tables (>10 rows), structured record listings, forms, and machine-readable file links. Full-spider counts are extrapolated from the section index pages and marked verified=false.",
  "headline_findings": [
    "Rich structured data is published as HTML tables, div-based record listings, and PDFs.",
    "ZERO machine-readable downloads (CSV, XLS, XLSX, XML, JSON, GeoJSON) were found linked anywhere on the domain during sampling.",
    "The sitemap.xml declared in robots.txt returns the 404 page (broken sitemap).",
    "Legacy backends surface directly in URLs (e.g. .php endpoints under /sub_your_park/).",
    "There is no developer/API/open-data page on the domain; the interactive Tree Map (tree-map.nycgovparks.org) is the only app-like data surface."
  ],
